<law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection amended="yes" chaptername="Cities Of The Primary Class" statutenumber="15-315"><bookinfo>Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2020</bookinfo><statuteno>15-315</statuteno><catchline>Mayor; remission of fines; pardons.</catchline><para>The mayor of a city of the primary class shall have the power to remit fines and forfeitures and to grant reprieves and pardons for all offenses arising under the ordinances of the city.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1901, c. 16, &#167; 29, p. 79; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 4492; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 3878; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 15-315; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 15-315; </para><para>Laws 2020, LB1003, &#167; 92. </para></source></law>
